    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAAdn//btg\u003d",
        "filename": "src/dsp/enc_avx2.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 785,
      "author": {
        "id": 1108495
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-08-14T22:17:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Pascal,\n\nThat\u0027s not similar.\nbecause Im not choosing here between using SSE4x4 of sse2 or avx2.\nThose functions are done only for my new version of PickBestIntra4.\nThe pointers are done between the regular PickBestIntra4 to my avx2 PickBestIntra4.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAAdn//buA\u003d",
      "revId": "a7dd7d4c3412ed314abe4709e11c7bff3f86bfae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAAdn//bsk\u003d",
        "filename": "src/dsp/enc_avx2.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 785,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000898
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-08-14T22:43:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if you change the interface (that is, the function pointers), you will have to change *all* the implementations: SSE2, ARM, MIPS, etc. One can\u0027t have one platform doing something differently from the others.\n\nAnd you have to have C-fallback too, note.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAAdn//btg\u003d",
      "revId": "a7dd7d4c3412ed314abe4709e11c7bff3f86bfae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAAdn//bng\u003d",
        "filename": "src/dsp/enc_avx2.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 785,
      "author": {
        "id": 1108495
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-08-15T16:36:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Pascal,\n\nAll the AVX2 functions that are implemented here have different prototype (get different parameters) then the one that defined in the enc_sse2.c thats why I renamed the AVX2 functions differently (from SSE4x4 -\u003e SSE4x4x2).\nIn my commit the only pointers that needed to be added is only  for PickBestIntra4(I didn\u0027t commit it yet).\n\nThanks,\nTamar",
      "parentUuid": "AAAAdn//bsk\u003d",
      "revId": "a7dd7d4c3412ed314abe4709e11c7bff3f86bfae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAAdn//bms\u003d",
        "filename": "src/dsp/enc_avx2.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 785,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000898
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-08-15T17:16:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not a good long-term idea to have platform-specific API for the dsp functions.\nThey are meant to be at a high-enough level of abstraction, so that they are common to all platforms and we can hide the specifics in the implementation.\nThis way, people with a new platform can quickly understand what they need to re-implement by looking at the other codes (or the C-fallback implementation).\n\nIf you thinkg to need to change the interface, it probably means the current API is not high-level enough to be common, and this should be changed *first*, before implementing the AVX2-specific variation underneath.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAAdn//bng\u003d",
      "revId": "a7dd7d4c3412ed314abe4709e11c7bff3f86bfae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    }
  ]
